what happened last night?

30
00:02:59,761 --> 00:03:00,571
Mhm.

31
00:03:02,291 --> 00:03:03,871
I'll tell you about it.

32
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:13,441
Jomkwan called Van "Pimpa, my chum."

33
00:03:17,111 --> 00:03:18,741
And said something along the lines of

34
00:03:19,671 --> 00:03:21,341
being betrayed by her friend.

35
00:03:25,551 --> 00:03:27,201
Granny Penn was her mother,

36
00:03:28,381 --> 00:03:29,741
and Van was her best friend.

37
00:03:34,461 --> 00:03:35,671
I think...

38
00:03:36,831 --> 00:03:40,831
she's going after everyone
who was involved.

39
00:03:44,441 --> 00:03:46,301
What else did she say?

40
00:03:50,611 --> 00:03:51,611
No.

41
00:03:53,781 --> 00:03:55,441
But Van told me

42
00:03:56,051 --> 00:03:59,071
to find the picture frame
in the hallway to the right.

43
00:05:13,821 --> 00:05:15,401
You used to live here, didn't you?

44
00:05:20,031 --> 00:05:23,031
[Jomkwan Norakankul, February 24, 1972]

45
00:05:25,701 --> 00:05:26,771
What's so funny?

46
00:05:27,341 --> 00:05:28,341
Spit it out.

47
00:05:29,841 --> 00:05:32,641
Is this the one, I wonder?

48
00:05:35,111 --> 00:05:36,501
Tick-tock.

49
00:05:36,781 --> 00:05:38,081
Tick-tock.

50
00:05:47,421 --> 00:05:49,921
[Your search on 'Jomkwan Norakankul'
did not match any documents]

51
00:05:54,931 --> 00:05:55,871
Boon,

52
00:05:56,801 --> 00:05:58,701
can you meditate, use clairvoyance,

53
00:05:58,741 --> 00:06:02,271
or touch an object and see its past life?

54
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:06,271
I can't.

55
00:06:06,641 --> 00:06:08,341
I'm not that good just yet.

56
00:06:24,061 --> 00:06:25,741
We need to search for the home

57
00:06:26,031 --> 00:06:27,621
in this picture.

58
00:06:32,631 --> 00:06:34,471
Follow the prophecy
to the woods before your eyes...

59
00:06:36,241 --> 00:06:37,871
Follow the prophecy
to the woods before your eyes!

60
00:06:39,281 --> 00:06:40,671
The place shown in this picture

61
00:06:40,941 --> 00:06:43,701
might be the same one
Granny Penn told us about.

62
00:06:47,841 --> 00:06:48,601
Mhm.

63
00:06:51,721 --> 00:06:53,371
But I do think it's strange.

64
00:07:00,401 --> 00:07:01,901
Are you saying that...

65
00:07:03,431 --> 00:07:05,501
Granny Penn's hint

66
00:07:06,331 --> 00:07:08,541
might be part of Jomkwan's plan?

67
00:07:14,581 --> 00:07:15,401
Uh...

68
00:07:16,711 --> 00:07:17,941
How may I help you?

69
00:07:19,181 --> 00:07:20,181
Well...

70
00:07:20,521 --> 00:07:24,301
Do you happen to know
where the place in this picture is?

71
00:07:27,291 --> 00:07:28,941
Uh, I don't know, ma'am.

72
00:07:31,661 --> 00:07:35,731
It's just that this is such a beautiful
and antique location,

73
00:07:36,031 --> 00:07:38,971
so we'd love to know its history.

74
00:07:41,811 --> 00:07:44,241
You didn't hear it from me, alright?

75
00:07:45,811 --> 00:07:47,501
The decorations in this place

76
00:07:47,951 --> 00:07:49,871
are mostly vintage pieces.

77
00:07:50,251 --> 00:07:53,571
The owner bought
everything from the former owner.

78
00:07:54,221 --> 00:07:56,301
And who is the former owner?

79
00:07:57,021 --> 00:07:58,171
Hm...

80
00:07:59,161 --> 00:08:00,941
I'm not quite sure.

81
00:08:01,591 --> 00:08:04,228
But...Mr. Direk,

82
00:08:04,261 --> 00:08:07,641
the former manager, used to say

83
00:08:08,171 --> 00:08:10,801
that it was the property
of the Norakankul family.

84
00:08:15,111 --> 00:08:17,801
And do you happen to know

85
00:08:18,241 --> 00:08:22,101
