86
00:08:48,641 --> 00:08:50,041
Excuse me!

87
00:08:50,641 --> 00:08:52,371
Is anyone home?

88
00:08:54,681 --> 00:08:56,241
Who are you here to see, may I ask?

89
00:08:56,841 --> 00:08:58,541
I'm here to see Mr. Direk.

90
00:08:59,351 --> 00:09:01,371
Oh, you're not from the North?

91
00:09:01,691 --> 00:09:03,321
Where are you from, then?

92
00:09:03,641 --> 00:09:04,871
Bangkok, ma'am.

93
00:09:05,891 --> 00:09:07,741
Well, I think you just wasted a trip.

94
00:09:08,161 --> 00:09:09,701
He has already passed,

95
00:09:10,261 --> 00:09:11,671
and was just cremated this morning.

96
00:09:13,801 --> 00:09:14,861
Was he sick?

97
00:09:15,831 --> 00:09:17,001
He died of old age.

98
00:09:17,601 --> 00:09:19,501
He passed away peacefully in this home.

99
00:09:20,101 --> 00:09:22,671
So what business
do you have with him, dear?

100
00:09:27,581 --> 00:09:29,771
We wanted to ask
about the Norakankul family.

101
00:09:30,511 --> 00:09:31,641
Ah...

102
00:09:32,221 --> 00:09:33,941
The former owner of the resort, was it?

103
00:09:35,301 --> 00:09:36,841
I used to work there.

104
00:09:38,121 --> 00:09:43,941
Would you mind telling us about that family?

105
00:09:48,901 --> 00:09:49,971
Come in.

106
00:09:55,371 --> 00:09:56,241
Wait.

107
00:10:37,651 --> 00:10:41,071
